&lt;p&gt;The Resuscitation Team arelooking for an enthusiastic part-time instructor to help with the delivery of mandatory training and other resuscitation-based training. You will be working 18.75 hours per weekon a Permanent contract.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Main responsibilities will be at Torbay Hospital with additional duties across the ICO. Youwill deliver resuscitation training and assessment across the ICO. This may include delivery to the Private, Voluntary and Independent Sector.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information regarding the job role, responsibilities and entry requirements, please see the combined job description and person specification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have had some experience with resuscitation and want to develop skills in training a wide range of different staff groups, then this could be a great opportunity to join a dynamic and friendly team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full induction and training will be provided on commencement to the post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information please contact Glynn Andrews Resuscitation Officer on 01803 656653. (Internal ext. 56653)&lt;/p&gt;
